_:N9d4f4e5127ec4b5bbf6e1c70f3b96ee4 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Professor Dame Diane Coyle is the Bennett Professor of Public Policy at the University of Cambridge where she co-directs the Bennett Institute, heading research under the themes of progress and productivity.</p>\n\n<p>Diane is also a Director of the Productivity Institute and a member of the government’s New Towns Taskforce. She has served in public service roles including as Vice Chair of the BBC Trust, a member of the Competition Commission, a member of the Migration Advisory Committee and a member of the Natural Capital Committee.</p>\n\n<p>Diane was Professor of Economics at the University of Manchester until March 2018. She was awarded a Damehood in 2023 for her contribution to economic policy.</p>\n" .
<https://www.gov.uk/> <http://schema.org/name> "Home" .
